quran[26]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,51,"Then you, O misguided deniers,",""
  56,52,"will surely eat from the tree of zaqqūm<sup>6</sup>,","[6] See footnote 44:43-46."
  56,53,"filling your bellies with it,",""
  56,54,"and drinking scalding water on top of it,",""
  56,55,"drinking like thirsty camels do.”",""
  56,56,"This will be their welcome on the Day of Judgment.",""
  56,57,"It is We Who created you; why do you not then believe [in resurrection]?",""
  56,58,"Have you thought about the semen that you emit?",""
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or is it We Who are the Creators?",""
  56,60,"We have ordained death among you, and nothing can overcome us",""
  56,61,"from transforming you and recreating you in forms that you do not know<sup>7</sup>.","[7] Or ""from replacing you by others like yourselves [in this life] and creating you [in the Hereafter] in that which you do not know."""
  56,62,"You are well aware of the first creation; why do you not then take heed?",""
  56,63,"Have you thought about what you sow?",""
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it to grow, or is it We Who make it grow?",""
  56,65,"If We willed, We could reduce your harvest to rubble, leaving you to wonder and lament,",""
  56,66,"“We suffered loss,",""
  56,67,"rather, we are deprived.”",""
  56,68,"Have you thought about the water that you drink?",""
  56,69,"Is it you who bring it down from the clouds, or is it We Who bring it down?",""
  56,70,"If We willed, We could make it salty; will you not then give thanks?",""
  56,71,"Have you thought about the fire that you kindle?",""
  56,72,"Is it you who produced its trees<sup>8</sup>, or is it We Who produced it?","[8] Referring to Arabian trees, markh and ‘afār, which produce fire when their green branches are rubbed against each other."
  56,73,"We made it a reminder [of the Hellfire] and a benefit for the travelers<sup>9</sup>.","[9] By which they ignite fire. Travelers are mentioned in particular because it is of special convenience to them, although it is of use for all people in general."
  56,74,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great.",""
  56,75,"I do swear<sup>10</sup> by the positions of the stars –","[10] The negative article ""la"" (nay) means: The truth is not what is said or thought by disbelievers or others. The oath refutes certain objections of the disbelievers with regard to the Qur’an."
  56,76,"and this is indeed a great oath, if only you knew –",""
